         <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>to <supplied reason="lost">the most noble</supplied> Caesar, <supplied reason="lost">Flavius</supplied> 
               Valerius Constan<supplied reason="lost">t</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>; 
               the Lepcitanians, devoted to his divine power and majesty, <supplied reason="subaudible">set this up</supplied> publicly.</p></div>
         
         <div type="translation" source="#tantillo2010" xml:lang="it">
            <p> . . . al nobilissimo Cesare, Flavio Valerio Costanzo (?), i Leptitani, devoti al suo nume e alla sua maestà, a spese pubbliche.</p></div>
         <div type="translation" source="#lsa" xml:lang="en"><p>To the most powerful and most noble Caesar, Flavius Valerius Constantius; the people of Lepcis (Lepcitani), 
            devoted to his divine spirit and majesty, [set this up] with public funds.</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Most probably Constantius I, Caesar 293-305; less likely, Constantine I, Caesar 306-307.</p>
         </div>
